# Idle / Clicker — Project Configuration

## Project Overview
- **Unity Version:** 2022.3 LTS
- **Render Pipeline:** URP (UI-heavy, very low GPU load)
- **Genre:** Idle / clicker / incremental
- **Target Platform:** PC (Steam) + Console (PS5 / Xbox)
- **Target FPS:** 60 baseline; throttle the tick rate when the window is unfocused

## Architecture

### Assembly Structure
```
MyGame.Core         — events, utilities, big number math
MyGame.Economy      — currencies, generators, upgrades, prestige
MyGame.Gameplay     — click handler, automation, milestones
MyGame.Meta         — offline progress, daily rewards, achievements
MyGame.UI           — currency display, upgrade list, prestige screen
MyGame.Systems      — audio, save, store/DLC, analytics, settings
```

### Key Systems
- **Currency System** — multiple currencies (gold, gems, prestige tokens)
- **Generator System** — auto-income sources, upgradeable
- **Upgrade System** — exponential cost scaling (cost × 1.15^level)
- **Click Income** — click to earn, upgradeable click value
- **Offline Progress** — calculate earnings while away (capped at 8hrs, 50% efficiency)
- **Prestige System** — reset progress for permanent multipliers
- **Daily Rewards** — consecutive day bonuses
- **Monetization** — premium up-front purchase, optional expansion/cosmetic DLC

### Scene Structure
- `S_Bootstrap` — persistent services (save, audio, store/DLC)
- `S_Game` — single scene (main game + all UI overlays)

## Skills to Load
- `idle-clicker` — big numbers, offline progress, prestige, upgrade trees
- `save-system` — auto-save on every purchase, offline time tracking
- `ui-toolkit` — upgrade lists, currency displays, animated counters
- `audio` — satisfying click sounds, milestone fanfares
- `dotween` — number counter animations, UI transitions

## Rules
Follow all rules in `.claude/rules/`. Platform guidance — PC/console performance budgets, input and
display handling — comes from `.claude/rules/pc-console.md`, which is always in force; there is no
platform skill to load.

## Key Conventions
- **Big numbers** — use formatted display (1.23K, 4.56M, 7.89B, etc.)
- **Auto-save** — save on every purchase, OnApplicationFocus (alt-tab), OnApplicationQuit
- **Offline progress** — calculate on launch, show "Welcome back!" popup
- **Idle-friendly frame budget** — 60fps when focused; drop to a low tick rate when the window is
  unfocused so the game is a good background citizen on desktop
- **Minimal Update** — update currency display every 0.1s, not every frame
- **Exponential scaling** — both costs and rewards grow exponentially
- **No skill required** — progress = time + strategic upgrade choices
- **Aspect ratios** — all UI anchors for 16:9 through ultrawide (21:9)
- **No push notifications** — desktop has no re-engagement push; the "Welcome back!" summary carries
  that weight instead

## Input Map
```
Player:
  Click to Earn — Left Mouse / A button
  Buy Upgrade — Left Mouse on upgrade row / A button
  Prestige — Left Mouse on prestige button / A button (with confirmation)
  Navigate — Tab and Shift+Tab / Shoulder buttons between tabs
```
Every binding is rebindable, and UI prompts follow the active device (see `.claude/rules/pc-console.md`).

## MCP Integration
Unity MCP at `http://localhost:8080/mcp`. Use for UI screen building and build configuration.
